            <p>POSTAL CARD.<lb/>
                WRITE THE ADDRESS ON THIS SIDE&#8212;THE MESSAGE ON THE OTHER<lb/></p>
            <p>Revd Mr. S. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>&#34;Jerusalem &#40;Holy City&#41; the Glory of all Lands.&#34;¬ù<lb/>
                ALFRED A. MARCUS&#44;<lb/>
                Diamond Merchant &#38; Importer&#44;<lb/>
                Purchaser of Real Estate &#40;Landed Property&#41;.<lb/>
                Residence 127 DARTMOUTH ST.<lb/></p>
            <p>No business will be transacted or interviews had on the Jewish Sabbath&#44;<lb/> from one hour before sunset on Friday until one hour after sunset on Saturday&#44;<lb/> or on the Jewish Festivals&#44; and no letters will be opened on those days.<lb/></p>
            <p>Boston&#44; Decr. 12 A. M. 5642.<lb/></p>
            <p>My very dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I have just this<lb/> moment recd. a letter<lb/> from Blessed Sir Moses<lb/> enclosing a letter for<lb/> Mrs. Garfield&#44; &#38; he sends<lb/> me a check of &#163;100<lb/> one hundred pounds Stg<lb/> to be distributed amongst<lb/> the different charities<lb/> in Boston without distinction<lb/> of race or creed in memory<lb/> of the late President James<lb/> A Garfield will write fully<lb/> tomorrow God Bless you Alfred A Marcus<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Please<lb/> shew this to<lb/> Mr. Jones &#38;<lb/> note it in<lb/> record.<lb/></p>
        </body>
